How we are different
Three pillars, presented as a three-column layout below the hero.
Behavioural compatibility
Compatibility is more than attraction. Long-term partnerships are built on communication style,
emotional regulation, attachment patterns, accountability and values alignment. Every introduction we
make is informed by an extended private consultation between you and one of our matching
consultants — a confidential conversation in which we come to understand your communication style,
your relational expectations, what you are looking for, and what is most likely to make a partnership
work for you.
Link: Read about the approach →
Professional matching consultants
Every introduction is curated by a human matching consultant. Our consultants are behavioural
interpreters, relationship strategists and trusted advisors. They make every introduction decision
personally, working within structured frameworks rather than relying on intuition alone.
Link: Read about the process →
Privacy and discretion
Privacy is foundational. Your application, your private consultation, and every introduction we make for
you remain entirely confidential. Your name and personal information are never displayed publicly or
shared with third parties — no public profile, no reviews, no visibility. Every member is identity-verified.
Introductions are blind dates — no photographs are shared in advance, on the principle that we curate
around behavioural and lifestyle compatibility, not photographic preference.
Link: Read about privacy and verification →
Who we serve
TrustMatch is for affluent, time-poor professional adults aged thirty to fifty-five seeking long-term
partnership. Our members are senior professionals, founders &amp; business owners, executives, family-
office members, and others who prefer to find a long-term partner privately, professionally and on their
own terms — whether they have left the dating-app environment or never wished to enter it. Our
members are predominantly across Melbourne and Sydney.
Membership
A tiered membership. Three core membership tiers and one bespoke Concierge engagement. Both men
and women pay membership fees; pricing is uniform across genders.

Foundation — from AUD 3,500
A 6-month curated introductions programme. The credible entry point.
Signature — from AUD 7,500
A 12-month engagement with deeper behavioural work and more introductions. Our most common tier.
Executive — from AUD 12,000
A 12-month higher-touch engagement with a dedicated senior matching consultant and one fashion
styling session.
Concierge (VIP) — from AUD 15,000
Bespoke. By private enquiry. For executives, founders &amp; business owners, public figures and members
with elevated privacy or reputational sensitivity.

